## threats and vulnerabilities ##

__Threat:__ ANYTHING that can cause harm, loss, damage, or compromise a system or technology. <br>
- natural disasters
- cyber-attacks
- data integrity breaches
- disclosure of confidential information
- critical vulnerabilities
__Vulnerabilities:__ ANY weakness in a systems design or implementation. <br>
- known software bugs
- misconfigured software
- improperly protected network devices
- missing security patches
- lack of physical security

*threats and vulnerabilites in combination is what makes something a security risk!*

__RISK MANAGEMENT__
finding different ways to minimize the likelihood of an outcome occuring and achieving the desired outcomes